<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586455>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 3. Concavistylon kvacekii gen. et sp. nov. from Moose Mountain flora, Oregon. a) Infructescence reflected light, holotype, UCMP 151875. b) Digital profile of the same infructescence, CT scan data, viewed through the sediment (rendered transparent) from behind. c) Raceme with several fruits showing styles concave toward fruit apex, UCMP 201233. d) Raceme with stout axis, UCMP 201232. e) Long slender specimen, with fruits spaced farther apart, possibly immature, UCMP 201231. f) Detail from (c), showing persistent styles, light microscopy. g) Detail from (b), CT scan surface rendering. Note 5 styles arising from upper left fruit. h) Infructescence with at least 18 fruits, reflected light, UF 18110-70163. i) Same specimen as (a), (b), (g), imaged with depth map rendering, showing apically opening capsules and 5 apically directed styles on each fruit, (j) same as (h), isosurface from CT scan data, showing apical opening of capsules. k) Depth map rendering of the specimen in (h), (j). Scale bars = 1 cm in (a–e), (h–j); 5 mm in (f), (g)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4586455/files/figure.png" .

